        "develop",
        "cherry-pick",
        "IoT_Industrial_PLC_Logic"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 2,
      "role": "Diagram_Editor",
      "action_type": "clarify",
      "utterance": "明白，这是一个典型的hotfix同步场景。我打算用LR横向布局，先画main分支的初始commit，然后分出develop分支。develop先有一个commit，之后切回main再提交一个标记为\"A\"的关键修复——这个\"A\"就是后续要cherry-pick的对象。这样理解对吗？",
      "elements_involved": [
        "LR",
        "main",
        "develop",
        "commit",
        "checkout",
        "A"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 3,
      "role": "Domain_Expert",
      "action_type": "confirm",
      "utterance": "对，完全正确。那个\"A\"提交是修复了PLC逻辑中的一个临界竞态条件，必须同步到develop。develop在cherry-pick之前还要再提交一次，体现并行开发的状态。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "A",
        "develop",
        "cherry-pick",
        "commit"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 4,
      "role": "Diagram_Editor",
      "action_type": "execute",
      "utterance": "好的，我来执行：先创建main分支的初始commit，然后branch出develop，develop提交一次，checkout回main提交id为\"A\"的commit，再checkout回develop提交一次，最后cherry-pick id \"A\"。这样develop就包含了那个关键修复。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "main",
        "develop",
        "commit",
        "branch",
        "checkout",
        "A",
        "cherry-pick"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 5,
      "role": "Domain_Expert",
      "action_type": "clarify",
      "utterance": "等等，develop上的第二次commit和cherry-pick的顺序没问题吧？我想确认cherry-pick是发生在develop的最新commit之后，而不是之前。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "develop",
        "commit",
        "cherry-pick",
        "A"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 6,
      "role": "Diagram_Editor",
      "action_type": "confirm",
      "utterance": "确认无误。develop的时间线是：第一次commit → 切回main做\"A\" → 切回develop做第二次commit → 最后cherry-pick \"A\"。所以\"A\"是挂在develop最新commit之后的，符合你的意图。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "develop",
        "commit",
        "checkout",
        "A",
        "cherry-pick"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
